  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Sick sinus syndrome with and without AV block and indication for first-time
             implantation of a DDD pacemaker: symptomatic sinus pauses (&gt;2 sec) or bradycardia with
             or without paroxysmal AF.

          -  Age â‰¥18 years.

          -  Patient informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Permanent or persisting (&gt;7 days) AF prior to implantation.

          -  Persisting symptomatic sinus bradycardia and/or chronotropic incompetence where
             DDD-pacing at a frequency of &gt;40 bpm is indicated (verified with long term ECG
             monitoring).

          -  Life expectancy &lt;2 years.

          -  Participation in another interventional research study.

          -  Indication for implantable cardioverter defibrillator (ICD) or cardiac
             resynchronization therapy (CRT).

          -  Pregnancy.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
